photo  corbis corbisimagescom  retrieved    john goben • webjournals webjournalsaceduau retrieved   blumhofer p  note reverend john d goben was a successful midwestern evangelist when he joined the angeles temple in  a revival campaign in  by goben led to the establishment the stone church in toronto canada goben served as treasurer to the international foursquare gospel lighthouses an association of satellite churches he helped manage because of a dispute with mcpherson and her legal counsel over property ownership by the churches he was ousted as treasurer his mounting discontent along with encouragement of some of the church board members in part precipitated his expensive private investigation of mcpherson one evening at a board meeting goben hoping to elicit a confession in lieu of evidence he could not obtain confronted mcpherson with his surveillance but mcpherson so shocked by what he did fainted the board members turned against goben and he was fired his bitter departure resulted in his publication of a pamphlet entitled aimee the gospel golddigger aimed at temple supporters he detailed alleged financial irregularities a brief grand jury investigation was started but come to nothing  epstein pp    a lasting legacy  foursquare legacy  the foursquare church foursquareorg retrieved    sutton pp    cox p  note mcpherson was frequently photographed with the image of the christian cross which differs from the crucifix with its hanging figure of jesus and its common association with catholicism cox states anecdotally some persons adversarial to mcpherson who heard the berle story wanted to believe it was true but that bit about the crucifix convinced them otherwise  sutton p   cox p   cox raymond l the verdict is in  p   blumhofer p   a b roberts liardon gods generals vol  dvd   sutton pp –  a b american experience  sister aimee pbs retrieved    she also traveled to england scotland and wales for five weeks of revival services press reports depending upon the sources described her audiences as either lacking enthusiasm or multitudes filling the altars anxiously awaiting a return visit poor aimee time october   archived from the original on  september  retrieved  those of the nobility and gentry and middle classes who reflected upon the matter appeared to feel that the holy bible still offers a sufficient choice of gospels but of course the london mob the lower classes rushed to attend the evangelistic first night of aimee semple mcpherson   epstein pp –  epstein p   blumhofer pp   note a month later most of the choir members returned their leader gladwyn nichols later returned as well after publicly apologizing to mcpherson  epstein p   epstein p   epstein p   a b epstein p   a b c dr raymond l cox  the greatest nine days oocitiesorg retrieved    epstein p   today in history  october  aimee semple mcpherson uninvited to speak at harvard skepticismorg  retrieved    mcpherson aimee semple give me my own god h c kinsey  company inc   matthew avery sutton aimee semple mcpherson and the resurrection of christian america cambridge harvard university press  p   mcpherson give me my own god pp –  dr raymond l cox  was aimee semple mcpherson pentecostal oocitiesorg retrieved    us  million in   us  million in   thomas storming pp   note splivalo did earn a loyal following of disciples at the angelus temple one in particular who was in contentious strife with mcpherson splivalo gathered a list of purported damaging statements together with the witnesses places and times they were allegedly made by mcpherson however the vocabulary of accused slanderous remarks as stated in the lawsuit were inconsistent with mcphersons known public sermons writings and statements  heraldjournal – may    united press april    epstein pp –  us  in   epstein p   epstein p   updike john famous aimee the new yorker retrieved    aimee semple mcpherson and the resurrection of christian america — matthew avery sutton  harvard university press hupharvardedu retr