angelism was popular in the united states she died on september   of shock and respiratory failure attributed to an overdose of sleeping pills   sister aimees death is ruled an accident united press international in the washington post october   retrieved  aimee semple mcpherson famous evangelist who occupied the headlines almost as often as the pulpit died of shock and respiratory failure from an accidental overdosage of sleeping capsules a coroners jury decided today    in  dollars  sutton p   bach marcus they have found a faith the bobbsmerrill company indianapolis  new york  p   about  in   about  in  dollars  about  million in  dollars  about us million in  dollars  epstein p   httpwwwfoursquareorg  cox p  note as one example cox lists a reporter for the los angeles times dial torgerson may   writes in his aimees disappearance remains a mystery story that hc benedict owner of the carmel cottage was expected to be a witness against mcpherson but died apparently of heart trouble before he could testify cox notes that hc benedict did indeed testify but on her behalf denying vehemently the woman with ormiston was mcpherson hc benedict died on november   some weeks after all testimony had been concluded  sutton p   sutton p   timothy tow john sung and the asian awakening articlesochristiancom retrieved    awake and go global prayer network  john sung towelmysitehostedcom retrieved    the real conversion of dr john sung rlhymersjrcom retrieved    george hunston williams rodney lawrence petersen calvin augustine pater the contentious triangle church state and university truman state university press  p   blumhofer pp  lian xi redeemed by fire the rise of popular christianity in modern china yale university press  p   dr edwin louis cole christianmensnetworkcom  retrieved    who is more powerful than the president mobilewndcom  retrieved    sutton pp –  epstein pp  –  sutton p   there is a god debate between aimee semple mcpherson fundamentalist and charles lee smith a