ssor of history and director of the institute for the study of american evangelicals at wheaton college wheaton illinois library journal▼▲ sister was one of the bestknown north american religious figures and media celebrities between the world wars at long last an objective and scholarly biography has been written about this controversial oldtime religion revival evangelist in this sensitive and engaging biography blumhofer a historian wheaton coll and editor  the christian century  depicts not only the woman who mixed piety and pageantry while crossing denominational lines but also the complex social scene of s america this volume outshines all other mcpherson biographies including robert bahrs least of all saints  lj  which is a speculative and dramatic recreation and the poet mark epsteins appreciative and noncritical sister aimee  lj  an excellent bibliographic essay is included appropriate for general readers as well as scholars this is recommended to public and academic libraries of all sizes gary p gillum brigham young univ provo ut publishers weekly▼▲ in this vibrant biography of controversial charismatic sister mcpherson  blumhofer  restoring the faith  traces the influence of the celebrity preacher on thcentury american protestantism seeking to separate the facts from the cloak of myth surrounding mcpherson the author chronicles the ontario farm girls religious formation by her mother by the flamboyant style of the canadian salvation army and by her pentecostal first husband robert semple who died when aimee was  and pregnant as the center of her international church of the foursquare gospel sister who married harold mcpherson in  built the angelus temple in los angeles drew overflow crowds to her assemblies and broadcast from her own radio station blumhofer explores the inner loneliness of this divorced mother of a daughter and son who served as sources for the study while marital scandals and the shifting economic and societal tides of the s dimmed mcphersons star today a purported  million members worldwide follow her vision balanced and engrossing this portrait also examines sisters early application of modern promotional techniques to a religious endeavor photos not seen by pw dec product reviews▼▲  stars out of   out of   stars   stars   stars   stars   star  quality  out of   out of  value  out of   out of  meets expectations  out of   out of   of customers would recommend this product to a friend write review sort by most recent overall rating helpfulness see    displaying items  of  page  of  pastor dale age  gender male  stars out of  good story of a woman of god september   pastor dale age  gender male quality  value  meets expectations  despite the problems that aimee semple mcpherson had in her lifetime her story is one about a woman who deeply desires to do gods will dr blumhofer does an exception job in retelling the story of aimee taking us back to her early canadian roots to her evangelistic career and then culminating in her death of accidental overdose in los angeles in  was this review helpful helpful votes yes   no  flag as inappropriate displaying items  of  page  of  ask a question▼▲ have a question about this product ask us here find related products▼▲ books ebooks  audio  nonfiction  biography  general biography authorartist review▼▲ im the authorartist and i want to review aimee semple mcpherson everybodys sister backtimes ask a question what would you like to know about this product please enter your name your email and your question regarding the product in the fields below and well answer you in the next  hours if you need immediate assistance regarding this product or any other please call christian to speak directly with a customer service representative name email question submit edit confirm sign up to receiveexclusive email offersyou can unsubscribe at any time sign up to receive exclusive email offersyou can unsubscribe at any time sign up connect with us account checkout account or